	   <tr><td colspan=2>During my creations of various characters and watching my friends characters play I reasoned that:<br>a) you are bound to get hit<br>b) make sure that hit does kill you<br>so to counter this I thought why not make a bard who can take the 2 or 3 stuns that creatures will whack you with and then Selo's out of harms way with a high Dex to make sure you get the song off instead of missing notes...<br>When finally creating my new bard (half-elf of course) I allocated points to dexterity and stamina...<br>Now she can take a few hits, get the song off and skipp out of harm's way... I let the armor do what it's supposed to... avoid the big blows.<br><br>I'd say stamina may be unhilighted but it should be... as all of you know bards are the last class that Verant should give the Taunt ablility to...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
